learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-23T21:26:29.280Z",claude-code-agent,"Manual compile test (scaffold a package per capability, symlink the SDK + @types/node, run tsc, then node --test) caught three real defects the JS scaffold never had to satisfy — none were caught by unit tests (which assert generated content, not compilation):\n\n1. `outDir: \".\"` → TS18003 \"No inputs were found\". tsc auto-EXCLUDES its own outDir, so an in-package outDir excludes the whole package root, leaving the `*.ts` includes unmatched and emitting nothing. Fix: drop outDir entirely and emit beside the source (mirrors first-party packages/pm-*).\n\n2. `node:test` / `node:assert` → TS2591 \"Cannot find name … Do you need to install type definitions for node?\". The colocated index.test.ts needs Node's ambient types. Fix: add `@types/node` (^20, the engines floor) to scaffold devDependencies AND set `\"types\": [\"node\"]` in the tsconfig (auto @types discovery did not pick up node: builtins under NodeNext in the validation harness).\n\n3. search sample fixtures → TS2740: `settings: {}` is typed `PmSettings` and the document `metadata` is `ItemMetadata`; minimal stubs fail strict TS. The importer for-test helper is ergonomic (all-optional + defaults) but the search/vector for-test helpers take the full context. Fix in the generated sample: `settings: {} as PmSettings` + `documents: [...] as ItemDocument[]` with imported types and an explanatory comment. FOLLOW-UP (pm-ax7z sibling): make the search/vector *ForTest context options ergonomic like the importer helper to remove these casts from every generated search test.\n\nValidation: all four capabilities (commands/hooks/search/importers) now compile with tsc rc=0, emit index.js + index.test.js, and pass `node --test` (4/6/6/6 tests, 0 failures)."
